        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 5:38PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 538 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located near Hidden Valley,
moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph and very heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Visibility will be poor and hydroplaning
is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Harrison, Cheviot, Lawrenceburg, Greendale, Aurora, Bright, Hidden
Valley, Cleves, Shawnee, Taylor Creek, Bridgetown, Miami Heights,
Blue Jay, Mack, Monfort Heights, Guilford, Wilmington, Logan,
Manchester, and Grandview.

This includes I-74 in Ohio between mile markers 0 and 11.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

Motorists should slow down and use extra caution.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
